1
00:00:57,033 --> 00:00:58,660
It all started when I was eight.

2
00:00:58,660 --> 00:00:59,994
After Mom's death.

3
00:01:00,120 --> 00:01:00,829
Uhh, Dad.

4
00:01:00,829 --> 00:01:02,914
Kaizer's inviting me to
go to Jerson's house.

5
00:01:02,914 --> 00:01:05,083
No, you don't have time
for such an immature play.

6
00:01:12,424 --> 00:01:13,550
At the age of 10,

7
00:01:13,717 --> 00:01:15,135
I learned how to pull...

8
00:01:15,135 --> 00:01:16,928
the trigger without mercy.

9
00:01:17,053 --> 00:01:18,972
Everyone around you
will die like your mother

10
00:01:18,972 --> 00:01:20,807
if you stay spineless like that!

11
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:21,391
Kill him!

12
00:01:21,474 --> 00:01:22,934
I love you, Zeke.

13
00:01:23,059 --> 00:01:26,146
Even if you were the
most evil person in the world.

14
00:01:34,112 --> 00:01:34,946
Oops! Porn!

15
00:01:35,822 --> 00:01:36,948
- What the fuck?!
- Shit! Not you, boss!

16
00:01:37,031 --> 00:01:39,200
- Mr. Roswell, wait! Don't!
- Don't!

17
00:01:39,534 --> 00:01:40,952
Where have you been, Auntie?

18
00:01:41,995 --> 00:01:43,538
I just went somewhere.

19
00:01:43,538 --> 00:01:44,347
Why?

20
00:01:44,372 --> 00:01:47,375
What if I can't bring
myself to kill the last target?

21
00:01:50,628 --> 00:01:52,464
Then you're dead.

22
00:01:53,131 --> 00:01:54,174
So is she.

23
00:02:17,572 --> 00:02:20,992
Finally, you have the courage
to pull out your gun.

24
00:02:21,451 --> 00:02:22,827
The question is,

25
00:02:23,286 --> 00:02:26,664
do you have the guts to pull
the trigger, Nico Jeisz Young?

26
00:02:35,006 --> 00:02:36,925
Do you know the real me, Young?

27
00:02:41,721 --> 00:02:43,807
Neophyte.

28
00:02:53,358 --> 00:02:54,776
Sorry, Dong.

29
00:03:48,413 --> 00:03:49,444
Are you okay?

30
00:03:50,147 --> 00:03:51,249
I accidentally

31
00:03:51,249 --> 00:03:51,875
pulled the trigger.

32
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:53,209
I was just aiming.

33
00:03:54,836 --> 00:03:56,462
I told you to be careful.

34
00:04:40,423 --> 00:04:42,258
That's why I love you, babe.

35
00:04:42,675 --> 00:04:43,801
I know, right?

36
00:04:49,432 --> 00:04:50,892
Why are you here?

37
00:04:56,606 --> 00:04:57,941
Are you nuts?

38
00:05:01,611 --> 00:05:04,238
Do you know what
you just walked into?

39
00:05:06,324 --> 00:05:08,743
I'm looking for answers
to my questions.

40
00:05:10,161 --> 00:05:14,832
And you think this place has
answers to your questions?

41
00:05:18,795 --> 00:05:20,630
This place feels familiar.

42
00:05:22,006 --> 00:05:23,257
Every corner.

43
00:05:25,009 --> 00:05:28,137
I feel like I've
seen them before.

44
00:05:29,639 --> 00:05:31,975
I've definitely
been here before.

45
00:05:33,351 --> 00:05:34,435
You're funny.

46
00:05:34,644 --> 00:05:37,438
Do you know how
dangerous this place is?

47
00:05:39,190 --> 00:05:41,901
Do you even know what
you just walked into?

48
00:05:45,822 --> 00:05:50,284
Something's telling me it
might not be dangerous.

49
00:05:51,903 --> 00:05:53,238
At least not for me.

50
00:05:56,207 --> 00:05:57,250
Well.

51
00:05:58,501 --> 00:06:01,546
Since I saw you walk in here,

52
00:06:02,505 --> 00:06:06,342
I can't exactly let you go.

53
00:06:06,843 --> 00:06:10,263
Unless you do me a favor.

54
00:06:13,099 --> 00:06:16,436
What makes you
think I'd do you a favor?

55
00:06:18,688 --> 00:06:20,648
Because I'm Cassandra Heather,

56
00:06:20,898 --> 00:06:25,319
and you're trespassing
in our territory.

57
00:06:25,945 --> 00:06:30,283
This is Mafia territory.

58
00:06:32,118 --> 00:06:33,215
Mafia?

59
00:06:41,169 --> 00:06:42,437
Cat's got your tongue?

60
00:06:42,462 --> 00:06:45,381
Were you surprised
when I said "Mafia"?

61
00:06:46,113 --> 00:06:47,782
I bet you're scared.

62
00:06:49,802 --> 00:06:50,762
No.

63
00:06:52,972 --> 00:06:54,932
Well, anyway.

64
00:06:55,224 --> 00:06:59,062
Judging from how you
look and your age,

65
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:02,273
I don't think you can
do my favor anyway.

66
00:07:04,776 --> 00:07:06,194
What's your favor?

67
00:07:07,904 --> 00:07:08,738
Nothing.

68
00:07:09,781 --> 00:07:11,157
I want you to kill

69
00:07:11,157 --> 00:07:13,242
Nico Jeisz Young.

70
00:07:14,994 --> 00:07:15,912
Nico?

71
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:19,457
That's my daughter's
friend. Why?

72
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:21,959
It's none of your business.

73
00:07:22,627 --> 00:07:23,961
Just do it for me.

74
00:07:24,712 --> 00:07:27,799
And in exchange for my favor,

75
00:07:28,091 --> 00:07:31,761
I can let you roam around for free

76
00:07:31,761 --> 00:07:35,014
as much as you want in our territory.

77
00:07:35,348 --> 00:07:38,059
So that you'll find the
answers you're looking for.

78
00:07:38,684 --> 00:07:42,355
Unless there's something
you want to ask me directly.

79
00:07:43,439 --> 00:07:45,191
I don't need your help.

80
00:07:46,025 --> 00:07:48,194
Well, suit yourself.

81
00:07:49,445 --> 00:07:51,405
You still have to do
me this favor, though.

82
00:07:51,948 --> 00:07:52,990
Fair warning though.

83
00:07:54,575 --> 00:07:56,702
If someone else sees you,

84
00:07:56,911 --> 00:07:59,330
they're not gonna be
as nice as me.

85
00:07:59,747 --> 00:08:02,333
So I suggest you be careful

86
00:08:02,333 --> 00:08:06,838
where you wander
in our territory.

87
00:08:08,589 --> 00:08:09,841
Like I said,

88
00:08:10,508 --> 00:08:12,009
I don't need your help.

89
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:14,178
And I don't need
your permission.

90
00:08:15,555 --> 00:08:17,515
I'm not going to kill Young.

91
00:08:19,225 --> 00:08:20,160
Well...

92
00:08:20,977 --> 00:08:24,564
what about I kill your daughter
and your niece instead?

93
00:08:28,192 --> 00:08:29,068
What?

94
00:08:30,695 --> 00:08:31,529
That's right.

95
00:08:32,196 --> 00:08:34,490
If you don't do my favor,

96
00:08:34,782 --> 00:08:37,410
I'm going to go after

97
00:08:37,410 --> 00:08:39,787
Aemie and Amesyl.

98
00:08:40,496 --> 00:08:41,561
Understood?

99
00:08:46,210 --> 00:08:47,003
Good.

100
00:08:47,003 --> 00:08:50,548
Now you can roam around
as much as you want.

101
00:08:51,090 --> 00:08:52,123
Go.

102
00:08:52,884 --> 00:08:53,889
Have fun.

103
00:09:54,737 --> 00:09:59,742
Of all the doors to open,
you just had to pick that one, huh?

104
00:10:00,743 --> 00:10:02,537
You really are a curious one.

105
00:10:04,072 --> 00:10:07,200
Oh, I've been in this mafia
for so many years.

106
00:10:07,667 --> 00:10:10,920
And me and my friends have
tried to break into that door

107
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:14,048
so many times, yet
we never succeeded.

108
00:10:14,340 --> 00:10:19,136
The only one that can get inside
that door is our boss.

109
00:10:19,637 --> 00:10:21,180
So don't even try.

110
00:10:21,722 --> 00:10:22,662
Understood?

111
00:10:25,059 --> 00:10:26,394
I'm going to leave now.

112
00:10:26,769 --> 00:10:29,021
If you wanna get out
of here alive,

113
00:10:29,855 --> 00:10:32,858
make sure you stay out
of the CCTV cameras.

114
00:10:33,734 --> 00:10:34,735
But don't worry,

115
00:10:35,278 --> 00:10:37,863
I'll be the one to check
it first tomorrow.

116
00:10:38,781 --> 00:10:40,032
In case you slip up,

117
00:10:41,409 --> 00:10:42,577
I can clear it.

118
00:10:48,249 --> 00:10:51,836
This room will hold
all our memories.

119
00:10:53,337 --> 00:10:56,311
I used your initials
and your birthday.

120
00:12:08,371 --> 00:12:09,372
Sylvia?

121
00:12:10,102 --> 00:12:12,496
No, you can't do this!

122
00:12:13,084 --> 00:12:14,185
Sylvia!

123
00:12:14,210 --> 00:12:15,920
I love you, Baby Amesyl.

124
00:12:51,122 --> 00:12:52,039
Eiji?

125
00:12:54,583 --> 00:12:56,961
Did I have a boyfriend named Eiji?

126
00:12:59,547 --> 00:13:00,631
Is this him?

127
00:13:24,738 --> 00:13:26,615
We looked so sweet together.

128
00:13:30,578 --> 00:13:33,873
We must've been a
very happy couple.

129
00:13:59,398 --> 00:14:00,733
Why did you stop?

130
00:14:01,484 --> 00:14:02,610
Are you okay?

131
00:14:02,776 --> 00:14:05,696
Alyana, we can't
outrun them anymore.

132
00:14:08,157 --> 00:14:09,492
What are you going to do?

133
00:14:11,789 --> 00:14:13,496
Take care of Amesyl.

134
00:14:13,996 --> 00:14:15,915
No, you can't do this!

135
00:14:15,915 --> 00:14:18,083
Alyana, I have to do this!

136
00:14:19,084 --> 00:14:20,127
You're pregnant.

137
00:14:20,669 --> 00:14:23,964
If I don't do this, we'll all die.

138
00:14:24,381 --> 00:14:27,134
Eiji and Alexander
are waiting for us.

139
00:14:27,301 --> 00:14:28,886
Alexander's gone.

140
00:14:29,762 --> 00:14:30,882
He's gone.

141
00:14:31,263 --> 00:14:32,473
They already got him.

142
00:14:33,724 --> 00:14:35,476
I don't want Amesyl
getting dragged into this.

143
00:14:36,352 --> 00:14:37,853
I don't want you to get hurt.

144
00:14:37,853 --> 00:14:39,355
You have to be strong.

145
00:14:40,648 --> 00:14:41,899
Take care of them.

146
00:14:44,985 --> 00:14:47,488
I'll say hi to Mom and Dad for you.

147
00:14:50,366 --> 00:14:51,509
Sylvia!

148
00:14:51,534 --> 00:14:53,327
I love you, Baby Amesyl.

149
00:15:02,670 --> 00:15:04,171
The Roswells are here!

150
00:15:04,713 --> 00:15:05,589
Sylvia!

151
00:15:26,735 --> 00:15:27,695
No!

152
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:35,687
Let's go!

153
00:16:51,070 --> 00:16:54,031
Finally, you're
awake, Ma'am Alyana.

154
00:16:54,643 --> 00:16:55,644
Who are you?

155
00:16:58,994 --> 00:17:00,079
Who am I?

156
00:17:04,083 --> 00:17:05,084
Where am I?

157
00:17:09,213 --> 00:17:10,257
Uhh.

158
00:17:12,424 --> 00:17:13,676
I'll get going for now.

159
00:17:14,593 --> 00:17:15,719
I'll come back later.

160
00:17:16,428 --> 00:17:17,971
Get some rest.

161
00:17:28,023 --> 00:17:29,608
Ma'am, your baby.

162
00:17:30,401 --> 00:17:31,320
My baby?

163
00:17:32,986 --> 00:17:34,113
When did I give birth?

164
00:17:34,113 --> 00:17:35,572
Just the other day, ma'am.

165
00:17:35,948 --> 00:17:38,033
We had to perform a C-section.

166
00:17:38,033 --> 00:17:40,786
You were in a coma
when you went into labor.

167
00:17:50,462 --> 00:17:51,617
I'll go ahead, ma'am.

168
00:17:58,721 --> 00:17:59,847
She's so cute.

169
00:18:01,306 --> 00:18:02,641
She really is my baby.

170
00:18:07,146 --> 00:18:09,606
So, how's my wife?

171
00:18:12,109 --> 00:18:13,132
Your wife?

172
00:18:15,446 --> 00:18:16,476
Where is she?

173
00:18:19,616 --> 00:18:21,452
Don't tell me my
daughter's your wife.

174
00:18:21,910 --> 00:18:22,970
Are you crazy?

175
00:18:22,995 --> 00:18:24,093
No.

176
00:18:24,538 --> 00:18:26,331
Of course, you're my wife.

177
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:30,586
Oh, right. The doctor said,

178
00:18:31,336 --> 00:18:34,965
now that you're awake, your
body needs time to recover because

179
00:18:35,257 --> 00:18:38,260
it'll be hard for you
to move around.

180
00:18:39,052 --> 00:18:41,346
You've been in a
coma for a long time.

181
00:18:43,265 --> 00:18:45,184
What do you mean under a coma?

182
00:18:45,350 --> 00:18:46,101
Look.

183
00:18:46,101 --> 00:18:48,061
I'm on top of the bed.

184
00:18:48,061 --> 00:18:49,271
Lying down.

185
00:18:50,037 --> 00:18:51,123
Coma!

186
00:18:51,148 --> 00:18:52,149
Not bed.

187
00:18:55,235 --> 00:18:57,070
Our baby's so
adorable, isn't she?

188
00:18:57,780 --> 00:18:58,843
Our baby?

189
00:19:02,326 --> 00:19:03,535
You're the father?

190
00:19:08,707 --> 00:19:10,375
Have you thought of...

191
00:19:11,293 --> 00:19:13,045
a name for her?

192
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:17,049
I waited for you to wake up because
I didn't want to decide on my own.

193
00:19:22,930 --> 00:19:24,515
What are you talking about?

194
00:19:25,557 --> 00:19:27,601
How is she your child?
She's my daughter.

195
00:19:27,601 --> 00:19:28,984
Are you out of your mind?

196
00:19:30,442 --> 00:19:31,776
She's our daughter.

197
00:19:33,023 --> 00:19:34,483
Don't you remember?

198
00:19:35,943 --> 00:19:37,402
I'm your husband.

199
00:19:37,945 --> 00:19:39,446
Miguel Romero.

200
00:19:40,614 --> 00:19:45,452
And you are Alyana Romero, my wife.

201
00:19:46,161 --> 00:19:47,830
The love of my life.

202
00:19:50,833 --> 00:19:53,126
Alyana Romero?

203
00:20:26,577 --> 00:20:27,744
I'm sorry, Nico.

204
00:20:28,871 --> 00:20:30,747
But now, you know the real me.

205
00:20:31,331 --> 00:20:33,792
I'm Alyana Heartily Ferrer.

206
00:20:34,710 --> 00:20:38,463
Daughter of a Mafia boss
and the wife of Eiji Ferrer.

207
00:20:39,172 --> 00:20:40,716
Tita, I'm sorry.

208
00:20:43,091 --> 00:20:45,012
I know how much
you love my daughter.

209
00:20:45,971 --> 00:20:48,223
And I know you would
do anything for her.

210
00:20:48,724 --> 00:20:49,600
Me too.

211
00:20:50,929 --> 00:20:53,723
I can't believe I let
her marry a Roswell.

212
00:20:57,520 --> 00:21:01,023
The main rival of my family.

213
00:21:44,571 --> 00:21:46,323
I know you saw everything.

214
00:21:46,990 --> 00:21:48,742
Whether on purpose or not.

215
00:21:52,663 --> 00:21:55,832
I will let you do the honor
of disposing Young's body.

216
00:21:58,627 --> 00:21:59,708
But, ma'am...

217
00:22:00,796 --> 00:22:03,757
Caileigh Ferrer is your
girlfriend, isn't she? Right?

218
00:22:09,429 --> 00:22:16,812
And I know about your little
sister, Milka Shinize Boulstridge.

219
00:22:16,812 --> 00:22:18,105
Am I right?

220
00:22:20,899 --> 00:22:21,525
But—

221
00:22:21,525 --> 00:22:23,318
But why are you
bringing them up, ma'am?

222
00:22:23,318 --> 00:22:26,029
I just want you to know that
I know everything about you.

223
00:22:27,447 --> 00:22:29,324
Vash Boulstridge.

224
00:22:30,242 --> 00:22:31,702
Your strengths,

225
00:22:32,202 --> 00:22:33,578
your weaknesses,

226
00:22:34,579 --> 00:22:35,789
your doubts,

227
00:22:36,373 --> 00:22:39,126
And all the secrets...

228
00:22:40,168 --> 00:22:43,338
you're keeping from
Ezekiel Roswell.

229
00:22:46,466 --> 00:22:47,718
Do I have a choice?

230
00:22:50,220 --> 00:22:51,471
Of course you do.

231
00:22:53,890 --> 00:22:55,851
You help me and I'll help you.

232
00:22:56,401 --> 00:22:57,544
But,

233
00:22:57,728 --> 00:22:59,062
if you refuse,

234
00:23:00,355 --> 00:23:03,692
I'll kill you and your loved ones.

235
00:23:06,069 --> 00:23:07,237
What kind of help?

236
00:23:07,821 --> 00:23:09,614
Keep an eye on Aemie.

237
00:23:12,284 --> 00:23:13,466
Done.

238
00:23:13,785 --> 00:23:16,955
And, help me find the truth.

239
00:23:17,998 --> 00:23:18,957
The truth?

240
00:23:20,375 --> 00:23:21,521
Ma'am.

241
00:23:46,818 --> 00:23:48,070
Auntie, are you okay?

242
00:23:52,199 --> 00:23:53,408
I'm fine.

243
00:24:01,750 --> 00:24:02,667
Oh, what do you need?

244
00:24:02,667 --> 00:24:04,086
Why are you calling, Wakwak?

245
00:24:04,211 --> 00:24:05,587
Momo, there's an emergency.

246
00:24:06,671 --> 00:24:08,715
Nico was rushed to the hospital.

247
00:24:09,549 --> 00:24:10,450
What?

248
00:24:11,343 --> 00:24:12,385
He's gone.

249
00:24:12,969 --> 00:24:13,857
Are you—

250
00:24:13,970 --> 00:24:15,263
Are you sure?

251
00:24:16,348 --> 00:24:17,933
I'm on my way there now.

252
00:24:21,228 --> 00:24:22,896
I'll just see you there. Okay?

253
00:24:22,896 --> 00:24:23,872
Okay.

254
00:24:24,815 --> 00:24:25,440
Okay, okay.

255
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:26,483
Where do I go?

256
00:24:26,483 --> 00:24:27,400
Where are you?

257
00:24:27,776 --> 00:24:29,111
In the hospital.

258
00:24:29,111 --> 00:24:30,052
Okay.

259
00:24:30,570 --> 00:24:31,905
I'll just send you the details.

260
00:24:34,991 --> 00:24:35,951
Niece.

261
00:24:37,911 --> 00:24:39,246
Is something wrong?

262
00:24:41,832 --> 00:24:43,250
Auntie, it's Nico.

263
00:24:49,417 --> 00:24:51,169
Auntie, they said Nico's gone.

264
00:24:56,972 --> 00:24:58,390
What happened?

265
00:24:59,933 --> 00:25:01,226
Auntie, I don't know.

266
00:25:01,935 --> 00:25:04,646
Birkins hasn't told
me everything yet, but

267
00:25:05,564 --> 00:25:07,190
I have to go, Auntie.

268
00:25:07,566 --> 00:25:08,733
Is Baby Ae there?

269
00:25:08,942 --> 00:25:10,068
Auntie, I don't know.

270
00:25:10,068 --> 00:25:12,863
But I'm sure
Birkins will tell her.

271
00:25:12,988 --> 00:25:14,099
I'm coming with you.

272
00:25:14,197 --> 00:25:14,948
Yes, Auntie.

273
00:25:15,115 --> 00:25:16,324
Okay, let's go.

274
00:25:16,867 --> 00:25:18,201
Let's go, come on.

275
00:25:25,375 --> 00:25:27,002
That's not fair.

276
00:25:27,836 --> 00:25:30,547
Why'd our training end so early?

277
00:25:30,547 --> 00:25:32,007
Don't rush things.

278
00:25:32,883 --> 00:25:34,426
There's always
tomorrow. Let's rest.

279
00:25:34,593 --> 00:25:35,635
Rest?

280
00:25:36,595 --> 00:25:38,471
Rest? I'm not even tired.

281
00:25:39,472 --> 00:25:41,349
And you're so unfair.

282
00:25:41,349 --> 00:25:43,727
You said you'd teach me.

283
00:25:44,186 --> 00:25:45,061
Yes.

284
00:25:45,270 --> 00:25:46,438
But be patient.

285
00:25:46,897 --> 00:25:49,065
You'll learn everything but
one at a time.

286
00:25:49,524 --> 00:25:50,333
Okay?

287
00:25:51,234 --> 00:25:52,110
Unfair.

288
00:25:54,237 --> 00:25:55,864
Life is really not fair.

289
00:25:56,198 --> 00:25:57,240
It is fair.

290
00:25:59,367 --> 00:26:00,619
If life is fair,

291
00:26:00,911 --> 00:26:02,120
can you explain to me

292
00:26:02,370 --> 00:26:05,165
why you have to compete
with others to succeed?

293
00:26:06,082 --> 00:26:07,459
If life is really fair,

294
00:26:08,043 --> 00:26:10,879
why do some people need
to sacrifice their lives

295
00:26:10,879 --> 00:26:12,672
so others can live in peace?

296
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,634
Whether you
like it or not, wife,

297
00:26:16,134 --> 00:26:17,135
life

298
00:26:17,135 --> 00:26:18,428
is really not fair.

299
00:26:21,223 --> 00:26:23,183
Why'd he suddenly
change the topic?

300
00:26:23,516 --> 00:26:25,435
I just wanted to
learn how to shoot.

301
00:26:27,395 --> 00:26:28,325
No.

302
00:26:28,980 --> 00:26:32,400
Being fair and unfair depends
on how we think.

303
00:26:32,943 --> 00:26:35,946
It depends on how we cope
with difficulties in life.

304
00:26:36,821 --> 00:26:37,982
I mean,

305
00:26:38,323 --> 00:26:39,279
look at me.

306
00:26:39,366 --> 00:26:40,909
I've never met my father.

307
00:26:41,576 --> 00:26:43,787
But I have my mother.

308
00:26:44,621 --> 00:26:45,914
I have my cousin.

309
00:26:46,873 --> 00:26:48,291
I have my friends.

310
00:26:49,584 --> 00:26:51,002
And I have you.

311
00:26:51,878 --> 00:26:55,757
All of you make me believe
my life is more than fair.

312
00:27:00,553 --> 00:27:03,723
Now I know why life is fair.

313
00:27:05,100 --> 00:27:07,435
You certainly make
me feel like it is.

314
00:27:31,293 --> 00:27:32,239
Hey!

315
00:27:33,420 --> 00:27:34,337
Louie!

316
00:27:34,838 --> 00:27:35,849
Oh?

317
00:27:38,657 --> 00:27:40,107
Uh, Aemie.

318
00:27:40,562 --> 00:27:43,583
Don't freak out, okay?

319
00:27:44,806 --> 00:27:45,765
Why?

320
00:27:45,765 --> 00:27:47,183
Are you going to scare me?

321
00:27:47,779 --> 00:27:49,825
No, uhh.

322
00:27:49,850 --> 00:27:51,059
It's just...

323
00:27:51,865 --> 00:27:53,492
Nico, Aemie...

324
00:27:54,065 --> 00:27:55,333
He's gone.

325
00:27:55,358 --> 00:27:56,239
Huh?

326
00:27:56,760 --> 00:27:58,637
Gone—but where did he go?

327
00:27:59,612 --> 00:28:01,656
That's not what I meant, Aemie.

328
00:28:03,575 --> 00:28:04,575
What?

329
00:28:05,118 --> 00:28:06,911
This guy's difficult to understand!

330
00:28:06,911 --> 00:28:08,538
Is he messing with me?

331
00:28:11,166 --> 00:28:14,161
Oh no, I'm starting
to sound like Zeke.

332
00:28:15,712 --> 00:28:17,422
What's that? You're
impossible to talk to!

333
00:28:17,714 --> 00:28:18,715
What do you mean?

334
00:28:20,175 --> 00:28:21,468
Nico's gone.

335
00:28:22,469 --> 00:28:23,470
He's dead.

336
00:28:27,432 --> 00:28:28,458
De—

337
00:28:32,020 --> 00:28:33,029
Dead?

338
00:28:35,148 --> 00:28:36,044
How—

339
00:28:37,359 --> 00:28:39,152
How did that happen? He was...

340
00:28:40,195 --> 00:28:41,780
He was still so young.

341
00:28:41,780 --> 00:28:43,406
And he was perfectly healthy.

342
00:28:43,406 --> 00:28:44,824
He wasn't even sick.

343
00:28:46,208 --> 00:28:47,247
And...

344
00:28:48,661 --> 00:28:50,580
He hadn't even finished—

345
00:28:50,580 --> 00:28:51,706
He still had so many...

346
00:28:55,710 --> 00:28:56,669
What—

347
00:29:01,758 --> 00:29:03,468
What happened?

348
00:29:20,568 --> 00:29:22,278
What happened to Moo?

349
00:29:44,426 --> 00:29:45,510
Moo.

350
00:29:47,429 --> 00:29:49,889
What really happened to you?

351
00:29:53,101 --> 00:29:54,727
You weren't even sick.

352
00:29:56,604 --> 00:29:59,376
I told you to exercise every day.

353
00:29:59,401 --> 00:30:00,569
But you're so stubborn.

354
00:30:08,783 --> 00:30:09,833
I missed you.

355
00:30:11,536 --> 00:30:12,787
Aww!

356
00:30:14,831 --> 00:30:15,957
Sorry, Moo.

357
00:30:18,011 --> 00:30:18,935
Moo?

358
00:30:25,383 --> 00:30:26,342
There.

359
00:30:27,051 --> 00:30:27,919
Okay.

360
00:31:08,551 --> 00:31:09,194
Hey.

361
00:31:09,219 --> 00:31:10,512
What's your
problem, Boulstridge?

362
00:31:11,269 --> 00:31:12,521
You've been like this for days.

363
00:31:14,182 --> 00:31:16,559
You're so deep in thought,
you look constipated.

364
00:31:18,686 --> 00:31:19,637
Nothing.

365
00:31:29,239 --> 00:31:30,240
Let's go.

366
00:31:34,702 --> 00:31:35,662
Zeke.

367
00:31:36,454 --> 00:31:38,623
I'm sleeping at Mom's tonight.

368
00:31:39,958 --> 00:31:40,770
What?

369
00:31:41,251 --> 00:31:42,152
No.

370
00:31:42,460 --> 00:31:43,527
You come with me.

371
00:31:43,878 --> 00:31:46,256
I can take good care
of my daughter, Roswell.

372
00:31:58,017 --> 00:31:58,926
Okay then.

373
00:32:23,126 --> 00:32:25,628
You guys think that the Yaji's
did this to Young?

374
00:32:28,131 --> 00:32:29,087
Maybe.

375
00:32:29,966 --> 00:32:31,759
But Young just joined Yaji.

376
00:32:32,510 --> 00:32:34,095
Why would they
take him out so soon?

377
00:32:35,430 --> 00:32:36,514
Shit, I just thought
of something.

378
00:32:36,821 --> 00:32:38,516
I found out something
about Kevin Alferez.

379
00:32:38,766 --> 00:32:40,024
He joined the mafia.

380
00:32:40,349 --> 00:32:42,225
Is it possible that it's
connected to Young's death?

381
00:32:42,395 --> 00:32:43,454
Alferez?

382
00:32:43,479 --> 00:32:45,023
- Mm.
- Ma'am Aemie's friend?

383
00:32:45,940 --> 00:32:47,483
The ex of Lamperouge's ex.

384
00:32:47,483 --> 00:32:48,587
Asshole.

385
00:32:49,777 --> 00:32:51,696
What Mafia did Alferez join?

386
00:32:52,488 --> 00:32:53,615
I don't know, but...

387
00:32:54,782 --> 00:32:56,492
Young was still new, right?

388
00:32:57,660 --> 00:32:58,995
If another Mafia took him out,

389
00:32:59,329 --> 00:33:00,872
what would they
even gain from it?

390
00:33:01,247 --> 00:33:03,249
Maybe they were
just fighting over a girl.

391
00:33:13,468 --> 00:33:14,517
Maybe...

392
00:33:16,054 --> 00:33:17,597
he found out a secret?

393
00:33:19,223 --> 00:33:20,173
Possible.

394
00:33:21,351 --> 00:33:24,854
But what kind of secret
could a neophyte uncover?

395
00:33:28,024 --> 00:33:29,525
What do you think, Boulstridge?

396
00:33:33,738 --> 00:33:34,781
I don't know, boss.

397
00:33:34,806 --> 00:33:36,766
But I don't think the Mafia did it.

398
00:33:39,160 --> 00:33:40,219
What the fuck, Boul!

399
00:33:40,244 --> 00:33:41,996
We've been talking
about that this whole time.

400
00:33:42,622 --> 00:33:44,155
You just weren't listening.

401
00:33:44,248 --> 00:33:45,958
Too busy thinking about girls.

402
00:33:47,213 --> 00:33:48,171
Morons.

403
00:33:51,506 --> 00:33:52,632
She needs to train.

404
00:33:56,135 --> 00:33:57,553
Aemie needs real training.

405
00:33:58,888 --> 00:34:01,182
I don't want to make the same
mistake as my father did.

406
00:34:04,310 --> 00:34:07,522
Boulstridge, keep an
eye on my wife's mother.

407
00:34:11,109 --> 00:34:12,171
Yes, boss.

408
00:34:12,568 --> 00:34:13,452
Wait.

409
00:34:14,278 --> 00:34:14,987
What are you
thinking, boss, and—

410
00:34:14,987 --> 00:34:17,281
None of your fucking
business, Lamperouge.

411
00:34:19,409 --> 00:34:20,366
Lerwick,

412
00:34:21,119 --> 00:34:23,913
investigate the Mafia group that
Kevin Alferez joined.

413
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:25,223
Find its name,

414
00:34:25,248 --> 00:34:27,208
who's leading it, how
many men they have,

415
00:34:27,208 --> 00:34:28,418
what business they hold.

416
00:34:28,626 --> 00:34:29,961
Find out everything about them.

417
00:34:30,303 --> 00:34:31,350
Report it to me.

418
00:34:31,879 --> 00:34:33,147
Got it, boss. I'll take care of it.

419
00:34:33,756 --> 00:34:34,710
Lee.

420
00:34:35,633 --> 00:34:39,053
Find out who the fuck is this
so-called guardian angel of my wife.

421
00:34:39,721 --> 00:34:41,139
My pleasure, Mr. Roswell.

422
00:34:41,597 --> 00:34:42,724
And you, Lamperouge.

423
00:34:43,349 --> 00:34:44,421
Boss.

424
00:34:44,851 --> 00:34:46,077
Keep an eye on Yaji.

425
00:34:46,352 --> 00:34:47,395
Yes, Mr. Roswell.

426
00:34:48,354 --> 00:34:49,233
What about me, Dong?

427
00:34:50,273 --> 00:34:51,327
What am I supposed to do?

428
00:34:53,025 --> 00:34:54,038
Hello?

429
00:34:54,986 --> 00:34:56,404
Hello, Ma'am Aemie.

430
00:34:59,025 --> 00:35:00,276
What the hell are you doing here?

431
00:35:02,243 --> 00:35:03,241
Uh, here?

432
00:35:04,078 --> 00:35:05,621
Standing, obviously.

433
00:35:12,044 --> 00:35:14,046
Did I give you guys
permission to laugh?

434
00:35:15,214 --> 00:35:16,174
Huh, assholes?

435
00:35:18,426 --> 00:35:19,469
How did you get here?

436
00:35:22,180 --> 00:35:23,973
I crawled my way here
while playing with Chinese garter.

437
00:35:26,100 --> 00:35:27,560
Then I did a flip
while looking up.

438
00:35:28,728 --> 00:35:29,741
Pretty impressive, huh?

439
00:35:31,522 --> 00:35:33,107
I'm just kidding!

440
00:35:33,107 --> 00:35:34,125
Come on.

441
00:35:34,150 --> 00:35:35,735
Mommy brought me here, of course.

442
00:35:37,111 --> 00:35:37,987
Where is she now?

443
00:35:39,655 --> 00:35:40,615
She already left.

444
00:35:41,115 --> 00:35:42,575
She said she had
somewhere else to be.

445
00:35:43,951 --> 00:35:44,660
You know.

446
00:35:45,328 --> 00:35:48,372
I'm actually a little worried
about mommy because...

447
00:35:48,539 --> 00:35:50,625
she's been going
out a lot lately.

448
00:35:54,962 --> 00:35:56,380
Boss, we're heading out.

449
00:36:01,427 --> 00:36:02,428
Bye, Aemie!

450
00:36:03,027 --> 00:36:04,168
Bye.

451
00:36:23,491 --> 00:36:24,543
Why, Dong?

452
00:36:43,177 --> 00:36:45,137
If you did it, just admit it.

453
00:36:45,680 --> 00:36:46,680
Me?

454
00:36:47,306 --> 00:36:48,224
Why would I?

455
00:36:48,933 --> 00:36:51,435
I couldn't care less
about that damn Young.

456
00:36:51,686 --> 00:36:52,867
I don't even know him.

457
00:36:58,442 --> 00:36:59,477
Blood?

458
00:37:02,113 --> 00:37:04,740
If it wasn't you,
then who killed him?

459
00:37:05,449 --> 00:37:07,034
Young was under Yaji's protection.

460
00:37:07,994 --> 00:37:09,579
He was training under us.

461
00:37:10,705 --> 00:37:12,623
Then why don't you ask Roswell?

462
00:37:13,026 --> 00:37:13,977
Right?

463
00:37:20,131 --> 00:37:21,173
Oh, come on.

464
00:37:32,685 --> 00:37:33,519
What's that?

465
00:37:34,645 --> 00:37:36,188
Nothing, nothing important.

466
00:37:44,322 --> 00:37:45,531
Jerson, let's go.

467
00:38:10,723 --> 00:38:12,016
Hey, Dong.

468
00:38:12,850 --> 00:38:15,603
Are you really not gonna
give me an assignment?

469
00:38:16,604 --> 00:38:17,730
Hey, Dong!

470
00:38:18,230 --> 00:38:20,608
Come on, give me
something to do!

471
00:38:21,108 --> 00:38:24,278
Dong, pay attention
to me, please!

472
00:38:43,422 --> 00:38:44,382
Hey, Dong!

473
00:38:45,257 --> 00:38:47,093
Dong!

474
00:38:47,593 --> 00:38:49,220
Yoo-hoo!

475
00:38:49,887 --> 00:38:51,806
Can you hear me?

476
00:38:52,723 --> 00:38:53,891
Dong, I got a joke.

477
00:38:54,225 --> 00:38:57,228
Why do you think the
carabao goes to the mud?

478
00:38:57,395 --> 00:38:58,312
You don't know?

479
00:38:58,938 --> 00:38:59,480
Well, obviously.

480
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:02,358
It's not like the mud's
gonna come to the carabao!

481
00:39:08,572 --> 00:39:09,573
Hey, Dong.

482
00:39:12,076 --> 00:39:14,412
- Please give me something to do.
- No!

483
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:20,501
Come on.

484
00:39:20,501 --> 00:39:23,879
I just want to know
what happened to Moo.

485
00:39:24,380 --> 00:39:26,590
He was perfectly healthy.

486
00:39:28,342 --> 00:39:30,177
He didn't die from an illness.

487
00:39:30,886 --> 00:39:31,887
He was shot.

488
00:39:37,184 --> 00:39:38,936
Who shot him?

489
00:39:40,644 --> 00:39:41,641
A cop?

490
00:39:43,024 --> 00:39:43,983
A soldier?

491
00:39:45,276 --> 00:39:47,486
Or maybe one of those people

492
00:39:47,737 --> 00:39:49,530
investigating his case?

493
00:39:52,366 --> 00:39:53,342
Insane.

494
00:39:53,367 --> 00:39:54,410
Not them.

495
00:39:56,787 --> 00:39:57,913
Then who?

496
00:40:04,211 --> 00:40:07,256
Oh, my god.

497
00:40:10,342 --> 00:40:11,290
Dong!

498
00:40:12,344 --> 00:40:14,346
Were you the one who shot Moo?

499
00:40:14,972 --> 00:40:16,079
Tell me the truth!

500
00:40:17,475 --> 00:40:18,392
What?

501
00:40:19,769 --> 00:40:21,437
Besides the police
and the military,

502
00:40:21,437 --> 00:40:23,314
you're the only one I
know who carries a gun.

503
00:40:26,669 --> 00:40:28,796
I thought he loved Moo.

504
00:40:30,237 --> 00:40:32,990
Maybe he killed him because
Moo had someone else.

505
00:40:35,493 --> 00:40:37,203
Oh, my!

506
00:40:38,662 --> 00:40:40,372
Ow! Why do you keep
flicking me? That hurts!

507
00:40:40,706 --> 00:40:42,249
Because you're
overthinking again.

508
00:40:43,250 --> 00:40:44,794
I did not kill him.

509
00:40:47,630 --> 00:40:49,840
Then who did? Why
won't you tell me?

510
00:40:53,135 --> 00:40:54,178
Look at this.

511
00:40:55,763 --> 00:40:56,806
What's this?

512
00:40:58,557 --> 00:40:59,433
That's Yaji.

513
00:41:00,726 --> 00:41:03,437
I'll give you 15 minutes to
memorize their background.

514
00:41:04,188 --> 00:41:04,789
Whoa.

515
00:41:04,814 --> 00:41:06,565
15 minutes? That's so fast.

516
00:41:21,038 --> 00:41:22,206
Oh.

517
00:41:26,335 --> 00:41:28,462
They look so cool, Dong.

518
00:41:40,683 --> 00:41:41,892
Lamperouge?

519
00:41:42,977 --> 00:41:45,354
Why does she have the
same last name as Kaizer?

520
00:41:47,022 --> 00:41:49,191
She's the sister of Lamperouge.

521
00:41:52,611 --> 00:41:54,697
Kaizer has a badass sister?

522
00:41:55,990 --> 00:41:59,243
And it says here she's
the brains of the group.

523
00:41:59,535 --> 00:42:01,370
She's the decision-maker and

524
00:42:01,996 --> 00:42:04,707
their lead strategist.

525
00:42:05,583 --> 00:42:06,584
So she's kind of like...

526
00:42:06,584 --> 00:42:09,003
the leader of a dance crew.

527
00:42:10,254 --> 00:42:11,213
Cool.

528
00:42:11,213 --> 00:42:12,631
They're not cool.

529
00:42:13,299 --> 00:42:17,011
And Kaizer has no idea his
sister joined the Yaji Mafia.

530
00:42:17,261 --> 00:42:19,138
after the death
of their parents.

531
00:42:21,098 --> 00:42:22,235
Oh?

532
00:42:23,267 --> 00:42:24,393
He doesn't know?

533
00:42:25,603 --> 00:42:27,897
Why hasn't he seen
these profiles yet?

534
00:42:28,772 --> 00:42:29,696
And...

535
00:42:30,130 --> 00:42:32,257
why don't you tell
him? You know.

536
00:42:33,277 --> 00:42:34,361
Why should I tell him?

537
00:42:35,237 --> 00:42:36,488
It's for him to find out.

538
00:42:37,114 --> 00:42:39,950
That's why I assigned
him to keep an eye on Yaji.

539
00:42:42,161 --> 00:42:44,663
Wow.

540
00:42:45,331 --> 00:42:47,791
You act like you
want to kill Kaizer.

541
00:42:47,791 --> 00:42:50,377
But you actually care about him.

542
00:42:50,377 --> 00:42:51,086
Stop that!

543
00:42:51,086 --> 00:42:51,587
Stop!

544
00:42:51,612 --> 00:42:52,415
Stop!

545
00:42:57,343 --> 00:42:59,595
I'm going to eliminate
them one by one.

546
00:43:00,554 --> 00:43:01,321
Huh?

547
00:43:02,055 --> 00:43:03,766
That's Kaizer's sister, Dong.

548
00:43:04,391 --> 00:43:05,451
What if—

549
00:43:05,476 --> 00:43:08,229
What if Kaizer gets mad
after you hurt his sister?

550
00:43:09,313 --> 00:43:11,065
Then I'll have to kill him too.

551
00:43:16,862 --> 00:43:17,864
Huh?

552
00:43:19,114 --> 00:43:21,158
Why are you showing me all this?

553
00:43:22,326 --> 00:43:23,410
Why do you think?

554
00:43:30,793 --> 00:43:31,895
Tomorrow.

555
00:43:32,127 --> 00:43:33,671
First thing in the morning,

556
00:43:33,963 --> 00:43:35,631
you're gonna start your real training.

557
